    "In the morning, everything was calm and fresh. I went into the garden and looked around. Several big branches had fallen from the old oak tree. There were puddles everywhere. But the sun was shining and the air smelled amazing — clean and cool. Dad said the garden needed a good drink of water. I looked at my sunflowers. They were standing up tall and bright, as if nothing had happened."
