  wordCount:158, readMins:3,
  blurb:"A moving van arrives next door — and a new friendship begins!",
  paragraphs:[
    "One morning in October, I woke up to a loud rumbling sound outside. I looked out of my bedroom window and saw a big orange removal van parked in front of the empty house next door. Two men were carrying heavy boxes and large pieces of furniture inside. Someone was moving in! I had wondered for weeks who our new neighbours would be.",
    "After breakfast, I sat on our front step and watched. A car arrived and a family got out. There was a mum, a dad, and a girl who looked about my age. She had curly red hair and was wearing a yellow raincoat. She stood on the pavement looking at the house. She did not look very happy. I wondered if she was sad about leaving her old home.",
    "Mum suggested I go and say hello. I felt nervous but I walked over anyway. The girl turned around and looked at me. I said hello and told her my name. She said her name was Orla and she had come from Ireland. She said she did not know anyone in this town yet. I told her I went to the local school and that it was a good school.",
    "Orla smiled for the first time. She asked if I wanted to see her bedroom. I said yes. We went upstairs and looked out of her window at the same street I could see from my window. We laughed because we could almost wave to each other. By the time I went home for lunch, we had already made plans to walk to school together on Monday. I was glad the house next door was not empty anymore."
  ],
