    "The first animal we saw was a huge brown cow called Daisy. She was standing in a field and chewing slowly. Mr. Webb showed us how to stroke her gently on the nose. She felt warm and soft. He also showed us how the cows are milked in the morning. I had no idea that so much work happened before the milk reached the supermarket.",
    "The best part of the day came at the end. Mr. Webb took us to a small barn and there, in a pile of golden straw, were six newborn lambs. They were only two days old. Their legs were very wobbly and they stayed close to their mothers. Mr. Webb let us each hold one. The lamb I held was tiny and white. It looked up at me with big dark eyes. I have never felt anything so soft in my life.",
    "On the coach home, everyone was talking at once about their favourite part of the day. Most people said the lambs. I agreed. I decided that when I grow up, I might like to work on a farm. Mr. Webb said that was a fine idea and waved us goodbye from the gate."
