    "Later, Nina's mum suggested she go and say hello. Nina felt shy but she took a deep breath and knocked on the neighbour's door. The girl answered. 'Hi, I'm Nina. I live next door.' The girl smiled. 'I'm Rosa. We just moved from Spain. My English is not very good yet.'",
    "'It sounds great to me,' said Nina kindly. She showed Rosa the local park and the corner shop. By the time they walked back home, they were already laughing together. Nina was glad she had knocked on that door."
