  blurb:"A dog living at a lighthouse helps rescue a sailor on a stormy night.",
  paragraphs:[
    "The lighthouse stood alone on a narrow strip of rock at the edge of the sea. For twelve years, a golden retriever named Copper had lived there with the keeper, Mr Haas. Every evening, Copper sat at the top of the stairs while Mr Haas switched on the great revolving light, and every morning the dog trotted down to the water's edge to watch the fishing boats return.",
    "One November night, a storm rolled in without warning. The waves crashed so high they sprayed the windows of the lighthouse itself. Copper paced the floor, whimpering softly, his ears flat. Then, above the howl of the wind, he heard something — a faint cry from below the rocks.",
    "Copper barked sharply and ran to Mr Haas, tugging at his sleeve until the old man followed him outside. Below, wedged between two rocks, was a small boat with a man clinging to its side. Mr Haas threw a rope and hauled the sailor to safety. They brought him inside, wrapped him in blankets, and gave him hot soup. Later, when the storm had passed, the sailor shook Copper's paw. 'Smart dog,' he said quietly. Mr Haas scratched behind Copper's ears. 'The smartest,' he agreed."
  ],
