    "I took it back to the library the next day. Mrs. Adeyemi, the librarian, asked what I thought. I said it was the best thing I had read. She nodded in the specific way she had that meant she already knew this. She had been saving it for me for a while, she said.",
    "I finished the sixth book on the last Saturday of the holidays. When I went to collect my certificate, Mrs. Adeyemi had written something extra on it in small handwriting: 'For a serious reader.' I have kept it."
