    {question:"What thought struck Yasmine about an unreadable language?",options:["She wondered how many hieroglyphics were in the alphabet","She thought about what it meant to exist in stone everywhere and say nothing anyone living could hear","She wondered how long it had taken to carve the wall","She thought about how difficult it must have been to learn"],correct:1,
     feedback:"'What it would mean for a language to be unreadable — to exist in stone everywhere, and to say nothing that anyone living could hear.'"},
    {question:"What did Yasmine do when she got home?",options:["She wrote a report for her school group","She emailed the museum to ask about the inscription","She tried to look up the symbols she had seen, and did not stop even though she did not get very far","She drew the symbols from memory"],correct:2,
     feedback:"'At home she tried to look up which symbols she had seen. She did not get very far, but she did not stop either.' — curiosity without a clear destination."}
